article.headline: Georgia Tech off to best start since '89-90
article.story:
ATLANTA (Ticker) -- B.J. Elder scored 17 points and Ismaa'il 
Muhammad added 16 off the bench to lead No. 10 Georgia Tech to a
75-62 victory over Saint Louis in the Peach Bowl Classic.

Jarrett Jack added 13 points and Clarence Moore chipped in nine
for the Yellow Jackets (8-0), who are off to their best start
since they were 10-0 in 1989-90.  They are three wins shy of
matching the best start in school history, set in 1992-63.

Josh Fisher led the Billikens (3-3) with 14 points. Reggie
Bryant added 13 and Tom Frericks had 10.

Will Bynum had six points in 11 minutes in his Georgia Tech
debut.  The transfer from Arizona was forced to sit out the
first eight games due to eligibility rules.
